A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 7 of Chapter 5 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to commercial drivers' licenses, so as to provide standards for liability of an
3 employer or insurance provider for actions relating to a commercial vehicle driver; to provide
4 for definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 7 of Chapter 5 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 commercial drivers' licenses, is amended by revising Code Section 40-5-145, relating to
10 duties of employer, as follows:
11 "40-5-145.
12 (a) Each employer shall require every commercial motor vehicle driver applicant to
13 provide the information specified in subsection (d) of Code Section 40-5-144.
14 (b) No employer may knowingly allow, require, permit, or authorize a driver to drive a
15 commercial motor vehicle during any period:
