16 (1) In which the driver has a driver's license suspended, revoked, or canceled by a any
17 state; has lost the privilege to drive a commercial motor vehicle in a any state; or has been
18 disqualified from driving a commercial motor vehicle;
19 (2) In which the driver has more than one driver's license;
20 (3) In which the driver, or the commercial motor vehicle that he or she is driving, or the
21 motor carrier operation, is subject to an out of service order; or
22 (4) In violation of a federal, state, or local law or regulation pertaining to
23 railroad-highway grade crossings.
24 (c)(1) As used in this subsection, the term:
25 (A) 'Driver's record' means investigation of a driver's safety performance history
26 through an enumeration of accidents and convictions of moving traffic violations as
27 provided by the department pursuant to Code Section 40-5-2.
28 (B) 'Federal requirements' means the number of years an employer of a commercial
29 motor vehicle driver is required to investigate of a driver's record pursuant to federal
30 law.
31 (2) For purposes of establishing liability of any employer or insurance provider in a civil
32 action relating to the holder of a commercial driver's license, use of:
33 (A) The driver's record shall be limited to federal requirements; and
34 (B) Any vehicle global positioning system data or video recordings, including
35 electronic control module data and any onboard electronic recording devices, shall be
36 limited to the date an accident or moving violation occurred."
37 SECTION 2.
38 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
